webResources.textAttributionSnippet: (en) Post mortem portrait of Esther Wallin. Daughter of the Laser Doctor in Vadstena, Axel Wallin and his wife Amalia Wallin. The girl was the couple’s first born child, but her luck only consisted of 1 year, 10 months and 26 days. The typhoid extinguished her life on February 17, 1874 - https://www.europeana.eu/item/73/S_OM_photo_OMEA0001240109. (en) Andersson, Anders.
